    interviewQuestion: "What NoSQL database would you use for storing IoT sensor readings?",
    modelAnswer: "Cassandra (column-family). Partition key: device_id. Clustering key: timestamp. Query pattern: 'get all readings for device X in the last hour' is a single partition scan — O(1) partition lookup, linear scan within. Write pattern: constant stream of new timestamps = pure appends = LSM tree optimal. TTL on rows for automatic cleanup. Alternative: InfluxDB (purpose-built time-series), Timescale (PostgreSQL extension).",
