    technicalDetail: "Social feed → Fan-out on write (push to followers' feeds) for most users. Pull-on-read for celebrities (> 1M followers). Hybrid for medium accounts. Redis list per user for feed storage. Cursor pagination on feed. File sync (Dropbox) → Chunked upload (4MB blocks), SHA-256 dedup per chunk, delta sync (only changed chunks), Merkle tree for sync state comparison, SSE/WebSocket for change notifications. Real-time chat → WebSocket for connected clients, message queue (Kafka) for delivery, offline inbox in DB queried on reconnect. Message ordering via sequence number per conversation. URL shortener → Base62 encoding of auto-increment ID (6 chars = 56B unique URLs), consistent hashing for multi-region, Redis cache for popular redirects. Rate limiting → Token bucket or sliding window counter in Redis, Lua script for atomic increment + TTL. Per API key or per IP. Typeahead/Autocomplete → Trie structure for prefix matching, Redis sorted sets (ZRANGEBYLEX) for top-K completions per prefix, Kafka + Spark to update frequencies in batch. Video streaming → Chunked upload → transcoding pipeline (FFmpeg → 240p/360p/720p/1080p) → HLS/DASH packaging → CDN distribution → adaptive bitrate player. Geospatial (Uber) → Geohash or H3 for location cells, Redis GEO commands (GEOADD, GEORADIUS), update driver location every 4s. Matching algorithm in separate service. Real-time collaboration → OT (Operational Transformation) or CRDT for concurrent edits, WebSocket for real-time sync, version history via event log.",
